## 4. AI / LLM patterns

### 4.1 Always use the wrapper
```ts
// ❌ WRONG
import { GoogleGenAI } from '@google/genai';
const ai = new GoogleGenAI({ apiKey: process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY });

// ✅ CORRECT
import { generateContent } from '@/lib/ai/gemini';
const result = await generateContent({
  model: 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview',
  operation: 'generate_html',          // logged to llm_usage
  workspaceId,
  generationId,
  contents: [...],
});
```

### 4.2 Streaming
- All user-facing AI operations (generation, edit) MUST stream via SSE.
- SSE event format:
  ```
  data: {"type":"progress","step":"analyzing_kb"}\n\n
  data: {"type":"partial_html","html":"<div..."}\n\n
  data: {"type":"done","generationId":"...","versionId":"...","htmlFinal":"...","pngUrl":"..."}\n\n
  ```
- Use `ReadableStream` API in Route Handlers. Don't use 3rd-party SSE libs.

### 4.3 Prompts
- System prompts live in `lib/ai/prompts/`. Each prompt exports a pure function: `(input) => Content[]`.
- **Few-shot examples mandatory** for `generate-html` and `edit-html`. Maintain 3-5 hand-crafted "gold" examples in `lib/ai/prompts/examples/`.
- **Never inline a long prompt in a Server Action or Route Handler.** Always import from `lib/ai/prompts/`.
- **Locked output constraints** in the generate-html prompt:
  - Single self-contained HTML document
  - Inline CSS only (or `<style>` tag in `<head>`)
  - Google Fonts via `@import` allowed
  - No external JS, no `<script>` tags
  - Exact viewport dimensions per format
  - No relative URLs (must be absolute or data URIs)

### 4.4 Cost tracking
- Every call to `lib/ai/gemini.ts` MUST insert into `llm_usage`. The wrapper handles this — don't bypass it.
- Pricing constants live in `lib/ai/pricing.ts`. Update when Google changes prices.

### 4.5 Editing AI = full HTML rewrite (MVP)
- **Do not** implement diff/patch or tool-calling editing. The AI receives current HTML + instruction, returns new full HTML.
- Each successful edit creates a new row in `generation_versions` with `triggered_by='ai_edit'`.
- The chat history (last 10 messages) goes into the prompt for context continuity.

