## 6. UI / UX rules

- **Editor page** (`generations/[genId]/page.tsx`) is the heaviest UI: split-view with Monaco (left) + iframe preview (right) + chat panel (bottom or right rail).
- **Iframe re-render strategy:** debounce manual edits at 500ms. For AI streaming, re-render on partial chunks if last chunk arrived >200ms ago, OR on completion.
- **Versions sidebar:** list versions descending, click to view, "Restore this version" button creates a NEW version (don't overwrite history).
- **Loading states:** every async operation has a loading state. Use Suspense + skeletons for Server Components, `useTransition` for Server Actions.
- **Errors:** show user-friendly errors. Log full error to `pino`. **Never** leak stack traces to users.
- **Keyboard shortcuts** in editor: `Cmd+S` saves manually edited HTML, `Cmd+Z` undoes manual edit (Monaco built-in), `Cmd+Enter` in chat input sends message.

