## 8. Environment variables

All env vars MUST be:
1. Documented in `.env.example` with comment explaining what they do
2. Validated at startup via `lib/env.ts` (Zod schema, fail-fast on missing)
3. Typed (`process.env.X` is `string | undefined` — never trust)

Required `.env`:
```
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://bannerwright:bannerwright@db:5432/bannerwright

# Auth (single user)
ADMIN_EMAIL=
ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH=             # argon2 hash
SESSION_SECRET=                  # 32+ random chars

# AI
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Storage
STORAGE_DRIVER=local             # 'local' | 's3' (s3 in v2)
STORAGE_PATH=./storage

# Optional: Sentry (off by default)
SENTRY_DSN=

# Limits
MAX_GENERATIONS_PER_DAY=100      # hard cap to prevent runaway costs
MAX_LLM_COST_USD_PER_DAY=10
```

